{
  "url": "https://www.hymnal.net/en/hymn/h/1241",
  "title": "God’s life and building can be seen",
  "verses": [
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "G",
              "text": "God's life"
            },
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "and"
            },
            {
              "chord": "D",
              "text": "building"
            },
            {
              "chord": "G",
              "text": "can be"
            },
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "seen"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With"
            },
            {
              "chord": "C",
              "text": "in the"
            },
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Song of"
            },
            {
              "chord": "G",
              "text": "Songs;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "He shows by"
            },
            {
              "chord": "D",
              "text": "types His"
            },
            {
              "chord": "G",
              "text": "seeking"
            },
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "ones,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The Bride for"
            },
            {
              "chord": "D7",
              "text": "whom Christ"
            },
            {
              "chord": "G",
              "text": "longs!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The Bride for"
            },
            {
              "chord": "D7",
              "text": "whom Christ"
            },
            {
              "chord": "G",
              "text": "longs!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As time goes by, her concepts change,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With dove’s eyes she can see"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "That naught can with her love compare—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "There’s none so dear as He!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A lily she is now to Him"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "(For still the Lord draws on),"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Her faith is not in earthly toil,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But in the wondrous Son."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "She’s next a dove who hides herself"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Within the cloven rock;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Now in her Lord’s ascended life"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Is love which knows no shock!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Of smoke, a pillar she’s become,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And now, as wand’ring ends,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Her wills to His will are subdued,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What fragrance sweet ascends!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Behold His couch . . . (O, can this be?)"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "E’en midst the fearsome night . . ."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "She now affords her Lord such rest,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The foe is put to flight!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A vessel to contain the King!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "(This type is full of worth.)"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A palanquin He’s made Himself"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For His move on the earth!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "8"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Of wood this vessel is composed:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Christ’s ris’n humanity."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Its silver pillars for support"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And floor of gold we see!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "9"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The seat of purple signifies"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Christ is of kings the King."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To Him, as fittings for within,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Their love His dear ones bring!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "10"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The day will come—(’tis surely soon)"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And glad will be Thy heart—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "What boast and glory to Thyself;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Thy crown, Thy counterpart!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "11"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A garden fair, enclosed is she"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "With spices, fragrant, sweet."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "She now brings forth materials"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The building to complete!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "12"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A city pleasant, comely, too;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "No greater building, this!"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "So beautiful, yet to the foe"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "A conq’ring army ’tis!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "13"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "As we eat Jesus, praise the Lord,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "The transformation’s done,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Until at last, the work’s complete—"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Christ and His Bride are one!"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "14"
    }
  ],
